==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: follow-through
<hw>follow-through</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Carrying a
process, plan, or project to full completion; <as>as, I appreciated his
<ex>follow-through</ex> on his promise</as>. The term usually is used in
reference to the period after some point in time at which the actor is
given freedom to pursue the project.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Golf, Baseball, Tennis)</fld> <def>The remainder of
a stroke with a club, bat, or racket after the ball has been
hit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>follow-up</ent>⟦br⟧
